PROJECT: L-CDEA (Lamina CDL–Discourse Execution Architecture)
MODULE: core/parser/

STATUS: core/cdl/ COMPLETE (verified + deterministic execution enforced)

---

# PURPOSE OF THIS MODULE

The parser is the **first semantic boundary layer**.

It converts raw input text into:

1. token stream
2. structured lexical units
3. pre-semantic candidate frames

It MUST NOT:
- assign final meaning
- resolve full types
- construct CDL graphs
- invoke MECP
- access DiscourseState

It ONLY prepares structured input for the compiler.

---

# POSITION IN PIPELINE

Input →
Parser →
Type Resolution →
CDL Compiler →
CAS →
MECP →
Executor →
DiscourseState →
Trace

---

# HARD INVARIANTS

1. Parser is stateless
2. Parser is deterministic
3. Parser produces NO semantic commitments
4. Parser cannot prune interpretations
5. Parser cannot rank meanings (no MECP influence)

